<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="540" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/473</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Netherland Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                                the Netherland Government wish the Netherland steamships <hi rend="italic">Jason, Cornelis</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">Amsteldyk</hi>, the charters of which expire shortly, to sail
                                for Argentine in order <pb facs="0655" n="1489" xml:id="pg_1489"/>
                                to load there grain for the Netherland Government. These ships can
                                eventually take a cargo from a United States port to Argentine.</p>
                            <p>I would very much appreciate if you would kindly let me know if said
                                ships will be able to obtain the necessary bunkers for their voyage
                                to Argentine and back to the United States.</p>
                            <p>As soon as final clearance from a United States port to Holland is
                                granted, ships of equivalent tonnage will leave Holland.</p>
                            <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. de Beaufort</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>